<refsection condition='ref.description'>
<title>Description</title>


<para>An anchor identifies a single spot in the content.  This may serve as
the target for a cross reference, for example, from a
<tag>Link</tag>.  The <tag class='element'>Anchor</tag> element may occur almost anywhere.
</para>

<para><tag class='element'>Anchor</tag> has the <tag
class='attribute'>Role</tag> attribute and all of the <link
linkend="common.attributes">common attributes</link> except <tag
class='attribute'>Lang</tag>.
</para>

<refsection><title>Processing expectations</title>
<para><tag class='element'>Anchor</tag> has no content and generally
produces no output.  It is a link target.
</para>
</refsection>


